Interface SOSearchListener

    • Method Detail

      • progressing

        void progressing(int page)
        Called to indicate that the search has progressed to a new page. May be called multiple times during a search.
        Parameters:
        page - current page being searched.

      • found

        void found(int page,
           android.graphics.RectF box)
        Called when the search terminates successfully. No further callbacks will be made.
        Parameters:
        page - page on which match found
        box - bounding box of match

      • notFound

        void notFound()
        Called when the search terminates unsuccessfully. No further callbacks will be made.

      • startOfDocument

        boolean startOfDocument()
        Called when the search reaches the start of the document.
        Returns:
        false to stop the search here - no further callbacks will be made. Return true to continue searching.

      • endOfDocument

        boolean endOfDocument()
        Called when the search reaches the end of the document.
        Returns:
        false to stop the search here - no further callbacks will be made. Return true to continue searching.

      • error

        void error()
        Called when the search encounters an error. No further callbacks will be made.

      • cancelled

        void cancelled()
        Called if the search is cancelled. No further callbacks will be made.
